      "raw_text": "SEATTLE, Dec. 21.-Thirty- nine\nsocialists, arrested on the charge\nof blocking the street at Pike place\nMonday night, who refused to work\non the chain gang, were released\nfrom Jail by Police Judge John B.\nGordon. Because the men had re-\nfused to work on the chain gang.\nthey had been ordered on a bread\nand water diet. Judge Gordon said\nthere was misunderstanding\nabout these cases at the trial. Upon\ntheir release from Jail the social\nlists formed in two columns and\nmarched up Second av."
